name: Neosephine Calorda
content:
Neosephine Calorda was a human TIE fighter pilot of the Galactic Empire whom the members of Hound Squadron, a A/SF-01 B-wing starfighter squadron in the New Republic, were taught to fear. Several weeks after the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, members of the B-wing squadron later listed Calorda alongside other feared rebel-hunters including Vult Skerris and Valen Rudor.
Neosephine Calorda was mentioned in the 2019 novel Alphabet Squadron, written by Alexander Freed.
